quran[39]{c,v,t}:
  23,36,What You have been promised is sheer nonsense
  23,37,"Life is only our worldly life: we live and die, but we will not be resurrected"
  23,38,"He is just a man who has invented a lie about God, and We will never believe him"
  23,39,"He said, \"My Lord, help me because they call me a liar"
  23,40,"[God] said, \"After a little while, they will surely regret [what they have said]"
  23,41,"So the blast justly struck them, and We swept them away like scum. Away then with the oppressive people"
  23,42,"After them, We gave rise to new generations"
  23,43,No community can speed up or hold back its appointed destiny
  23,44,"Then We sent Our Messengers in succession. Whenever a messenger came to a community he was invariably rejected, so We destroyed them one after the other, until they became mere tales. Away, then, with the people who do not believe"
  23,45,Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs and a clear authority
  23,46,"to Pharaoh and his inner circle, but they were an arrogant, haughty people"
  23,47,"They said, \"Should we believe two human beings like us while their people are serving us"
  23,48,"So they called them both liars, and were consequently destroyed"
  23,49,And We gave Moses the Book so that they might be guided
  23,50,"And We made the son of Mary and his mother a sign, and sheltered them within a hill where there was a meadow and a flowing spring"
  23,51,"[God said], \"O Messengers, eat good things and do good. I know all that you do"
  23,52,"This community of yours is one community, and I am your Lord, so be ever conscious of Me"
  23,53,"Yet [your followers] tore their unity piece by piece, each faction rejoicing in what it has"
  23,54,"So, leave them in their confusion for a while"
  23,55,Do they think that We provide them wealth and children
  23,56,"because We rush to give them good things? No, but they are oblivious [to what is going on]"
  23,57,Those who stand in awe of their Lord
  23,58,who believe in the messages of their Lord
  23,59,who do not associate anything with their Lord
  23,60,and who give whatever they can while their hearts tremble at the thought that they will be returning to their Lord
  23,61,"these are the ones who vie to do good deeds, and they will be the first to attain them"
  23,62,We do not burden any soul with more than it can bear. There is a record with Us which speaks the Truth and they will not be treated unjustly
  23,63,"However, the [unbelievers'] hearts are in confusion about this [message], and they do even do worse deeds"
  23,64,"until We bring those corrupted with opulence for punishment. Only then will they suddenly start crying [to God] for help"
  23,65,Do not cry out today. You will not get any help from Us
  23,66,"For [every time] My verses were recited to you, you turned away from them"
  23,67,"in arrogance, amusing yourself by talking nonsense about them far into the night"
  23,68,"Have they not thought about what We tell them, or has something come to them that did not come to their forefathers"
  23,69,Or do they not recognize their messenger? Is that why they do not acknowledge him
  23,70,"Or do they say, \"He is crazy?\" when in fact he brought them the Truth. But most of them hate the Truth"
  23,71,"If the Truth conformed to their desires, truly, the heavens, and the earth, and whoever is in them would have been corrupted. Instead, We have given them their Reminder, but they turn away from it"
  23,72,"Or [do they think that] you are asking them for compensation, when your Lord's compensation is best? He is the Best of Providers"
  23,73,You call them to a straight path
  23,74,but those who do not believe in the Hereafter deviate from that path